description: The lingo macro no longer changes the current tiddler while rendering a language string
impact-type: compatibility-break

Before v5.5.0, the <<.var lingo>> macro transcluded the language string tiddler directly, which set the <<.var currentTiddler>> variable to the language tiddler for the duration of the transclusion.

From v5.5.0 onwards, the language string is transcluded as a template, leaving <<.var currentTiddler>> unchanged. Most language strings are plain text and are unaffected. A language string that references <<.var currentTiddler>>, or uses a field reference such as `{{!!caption}}`, now resolves against the tiddler from which <<.var lingo>> was called rather than the language tiddler itself.
